<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 20 at 9:18PM EST  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...An intense lake effect snow band will affect southwestern
Medina...northeastern Ashland...northwestern Wayne and Lorain
Counties Until 1045 PM EST....
At 916 PM EST, radar indicated an intense lake effect snow band along
a line extending from near Lorain to near Grafton to near Lodi,
moving south southwest at 15 mph.
HAZARDS INCLUDE...
Visibility rapidly dropping to less than a quarter of a mile...
Locations that may be impacted include... Lorain, Elyria, Vermilion,
Western Vermilion, Amherst, Grafton, Wellington, Lodi, West Salem,
Oberlin, Sullivan, Lagrange, Penfield, South Amherst, Pittsfield,
Spencer, Kipton, Burbank, Congress and Rochester.
Use extra caution if you must travel into or through this lake effect
snow band. Rapid changes in visibility and potentially slick roads
are likely to lead to accidents. Consider delaying travel until this
snow band passes your location.
&amp;&amp;</description>
